<TITLE> Uttara university student beaten to death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka February 18 (bdnews24.com)--A student of a private university in Uttara died in hospital after allegedly being beaten by fellow students in an altercation over money matters, said police and relatives on Wednesday. The victim, 20 year-old Mahfuzul Rahman Nasim, a fashion design student at Santa Mariam University of Creative Technology, died Tuesday night, said officer in charge of Uttara Police Station Saiful Islam Chowdhury. University authorities announced a two-day closure for mourning, following the tragic incident. "A case was filed at the Uttara police and we have arrested one 'Rana' in connection with the killing," said Chowdhury. The victim's uncle Fariduddin, plaintiff in the case, told bdnews24.com, "Some friends of Nasim beat him up Tuesday afternoon over an issue involving money transactions." He said Nasim was taken to Apollo Hospital, where he died at around 9pm. Saiful Islam Chowdhury told bdnews24.com that Nasim and a friend had taken Tk 5,000 from others with the promise of purchasing alcoholic beverages for them. "But, Nasim failed to keep his promise and was physically assaulted on Tuesday." The OC added that a huge number of young students were involved in taking drugs or other intoxicating substances. bd
